commit.message: .github/workflows/test.yml: run unit tests as GitHub action

fix @resolve() with empty result

If the resolver returns no address (e.g. upon NXDOMAIN), ferm should
return an empty array instead of returning "undefined"; it should
suppress the calling rule instead of generating a broken one.

Closes https://github.com/MaxKellermann/ferm/issues/85

defer the cat() call if parameters are deferred

Fixes crash because cat() does not support deferred parameters.

Closes https://github.com/MaxKellermann/ferm/issues/86

test/resolve/with_cat: new unit test

Test part 2 of https://github.com/MaxKellermann/ferm/issues/86

recursive realize_deferred() call

To support nested deferred evaluation.

add realize_deferred() call to unfold_rule()

Fixes part 1 of https://github.com/MaxKellermann/ferm/issues/86

test/resolve/with_ipfilter: new unit test

Test part 1 of https://github.com/MaxKellermann/ferm/issues/86
stricter regex for numeric IPv6 addresses, require two colons
@resolve allows numeric IP address with netmask prefix
@resolve filters out numeric IP addresses for the wrong domain
NEWS: fix typo added by commit 23355141bb39f659acfd3af9d0cecd8d461ce965

fix negated @ipfilter/@resolve

For negated values, a `realize_deferred()` call was missing.

Regression by commit 31bb5d33a2b68ecf34f2a3855f239eae6ab9a670

Closes https://github.com/MaxKellermann/ferm/issues/78
